Author:
Vol / Page:  A4
Edition:
Quote:  The New Zealand fairy tern, once widespread in the North island, has teetered on the brink of extinction since the 1970s .. Fairy terns nest on shell and sand banks just above high tide .. The fairy tern now breeds at only four nesting sites, at Papakanui Spit, Pakiri, Waipu and Mangawhai.
